198
00:11:46.100 --> 00:11:46.140
<b>Who's-Who
Soaring Six
Ancient Cat-Cat Fruit: Saber-Toothed Tiger</b>

199
00:11:46.140 --> 00:11:46.190
<b>Who's-Who
Soaring Six
Ancient Cat-Cat Fruit: Saber-Toothed Tiger</b>

200
00:11:46.190 --> 00:11:46.230
<b>Who's-Who
Soaring Six
Ancient Cat-Cat Fruit: Saber-Toothed Tiger</b>

201
00:11:46.230 --> 00:11:46.270
<b>Who's-Who
Soaring Six
Ancient Cat-Cat Fruit: Saber-Toothed Tiger</b>

202
00:11:46.270 --> 00:11:46.310
<b>Who's-Who
Soaring Six
Ancient Cat-Cat Fruit: Saber-Toothed Tiger</b>

203
00:11:46.310 --> 00:11:48.310
<b>Who's-Who
Soaring Six
Ancient Cat-Cat Fruit: Saber-Toothed Tiger</b>

204
00:11:50.690 --> 00:11:56.280
Former Warlord Jinbe, Knight of the Sea,
acting with all the decorum of a child?

205
00:11:57.200 --> 00:12:01.080
I am the helmsman of the Straw Hats!

206
00:12:01.080 --> 00:12:04.080
Would you do me the honor
of using this worthier title?

207
00:12:04.080 --> 00:12:06.330
Oh, my bad.

208
00:12:06.910 --> 00:12:11.210
I caught a glimpse of you back in your Warlord days...

209
00:12:11.210 --> 00:12:12.420
What?!

210
00:12:13.130 --> 00:12:15.380
Well, it's no big deal.

211
00:12:15.380 --> 00:12:17.930
Who are you?

212
00:12:18.260 --> 00:12:21.010
Man, who could I possibly be?

213
00:12:21.010 --> 00:12:25.720
Perhaps removing your mask
will jog my memory.

214
00:12:27.940 --> 00:12:30.400
I'd love to see you try.

215
00:12:31.110 --> 00:12:33.650
<b>Forbidden Storehouse

Inside the Dome</b>

216
00:12:37.240 --> 00:12:40.910
We can hide here for a bit
since this room has long gone unnoticed.

217
00:12:41.490 --> 00:12:43.990
What am I seeing?

218
00:12:43.990 --> 00:12:45.660
A statue of a dragon.

219
00:12:45.660 --> 00:12:51.790
It once stood at the entry point of the island,
but it was placed in here after my friend broke it.

220
00:12:51.790 --> 00:12:53.090
Your friend?

221
00:12:53.500 --> 00:12:55.090
Yes...

222
00:12:55.090 --> 00:12:56.960
A few years ago...

223
00:12:57.760 --> 00:13:00.300
he came to kill my father!

224
00:13:09.560 --> 00:13:12.190
What gives? This place is deserted...

225
00:13:21.860 --> 00:13:23.660
Intruders!

226
00:13:24.330 --> 00:13:26.870
If you're not Kaido, get lost!

227
00:13:33.130 --> 00:13:34.250
Ace!

228
00:13:34.250 --> 00:13:36.800
Guys, go save the children while you can!

229
00:13:36.800 --> 00:13:38.010
Got it!

230
00:13:38.010 --> 00:13:38.960
Leave it to us!

231
00:13:41.760 --> 00:13:43.220
This one won't stay down!

232
00:13:49.180 --> 00:13:51.560
Who are you?! Tell me your name!

233
00:13:52.100 --> 00:13:53.650
Right back at you!

234
00:13:58.230 --> 00:13:59.990
I'm Ace!

235
00:13:59.990 --> 00:14:01.990
I'm here to take Kaido's head!

236
00:14:04.950 --> 00:14:07.330
I found them! Over here!

237
00:14:09.830 --> 00:14:13.080
Don't be scared. We're getting
all of you out of here.

238
00:14:13.080 --> 00:14:14.790
Yeah, but we need to hurry.

239
00:14:23.840 --> 00:14:25.720
You're pretty tough.

240
00:14:30.140 --> 00:14:31.100
Ace!

241
00:14:32.230 --> 00:14:34.310
All the children are okay!

242
00:14:34.310 --> 00:14:37.520
But we can't find Kaido anywhere!

243
00:14:37.520 --> 00:14:38.190
What?!

244
00:14:38.820 --> 00:14:40.860
My father went on an expedition!

245
00:14:40.860 --> 00:14:42.490
At this very moment...

246
00:14:42.860 --> 00:14:44.660
not a single officer is here!

247
00:14:45.030 --> 00:14:46.120
Your father?!

248
00:14:46.120 --> 00:14:47.530
– What?!
– What?!

249
00:14:47.530 --> 00:14:50.740
So she's Kaido's daughter?!

250
00:14:53.120 --> 00:14:54.420
I'm Yamato!

251
00:14:54.960 --> 00:14:58.340
I think it's about time you
stopped tearing up the place!

252
00:14:58.340 --> 00:15:00.460
If you have time to wonder who I am,

253
00:15:00.460 --> 00:15:05.380
then you have time to leave
and return these children to their families!

254
00:15:06.640 --> 00:15:08.300
I'll take you up on that.

255
00:15:08.890 --> 00:15:11.430
But is it wise to let us go?

256
00:15:11.430 --> 00:15:14.890
It's not like I'm under any obligation
to protect this island.

257
00:15:24.490 --> 00:15:27.160
Alright, let's get back to Wano.

258
00:15:27.160 --> 00:15:29.200
Your families are waiting for you.

259
00:15:29.580 --> 00:15:33.580
Truly, we can't thank you enough!

260
00:15:33.580 --> 00:15:35.290
You sure, Ace?

261
00:15:35.290 --> 00:15:38.130
That means going back
to the mainland without you.

262
00:15:38.130 --> 00:15:42.840
That's right. Keep them safe. I'll catch up later.

263
00:15:47.470 --> 00:15:51.760
I'm not convinced someone as strong
as you isn't at least one of their captains...

264
00:15:52.350 --> 00:15:53.680
Let's settle this!

265
00:15:53.680 --> 00:15:56.190
I was bored anyway.

266
00:15:56.190 --> 00:15:57.310
Let's fight!

267
00:16:08.530 --> 00:16:10.160
Fire Fist!

268
00:16:31.470 --> 00:16:35.430
What's the story? Shouldn't someone
as strong as you be out at sea?!

269
00:16:36.640 --> 00:16:38.850
It's all his fault...

270
00:16:39.600 --> 00:16:40.850
Kaido's fault!

271
00:16:41.940 --> 00:16:43.860
Of all the people to have as a father...

272
00:16:44.820 --> 00:16:47.820
It's all your father's fault?

273
00:16:48.610 --> 00:16:50.820
That's your excuse?

274
00:16:55.950 --> 00:16:57.620
You can't...

275
00:16:58.910 --> 00:17:01.540
choose your parents, Yamato!

276
00:17:02.170 --> 00:17:06.210
Shut up! Don't you think I know that?!

277
00:17:07.130 --> 00:17:09.260
Do you really?

278
00:17:10.760 --> 00:17:14.970
Physical shackles are one thing,
but if you hate your father this much...

279
00:17:14.970 --> 00:17:17.680
why shackle your heart as well?!

280
00:17:36.580 --> 00:17:38.120
Yamato!

281
00:17:38.120 --> 00:17:40.540
What do you want to do?!

282
00:18:14.160 --> 00:18:15.490
I admit...

283
00:18:16.280 --> 00:18:18.870
I was holding myself back.

284
00:18:20.160 --> 00:18:21.710
But now I realize...

285
00:18:22.620 --> 00:18:26.540
I wanna set out to sea and go on adventures!

286
00:18:27.090 --> 00:18:30.130
I wanna live freely like Oden!

287
00:18:31.130 --> 00:18:32.130
Set out to sea...

288
00:18:32.630 --> 00:18:34.260
To sea...

289
00:18:34.260 --> 00:18:36.470
I wanna leave this damn island...!

290
00:18:37.100 --> 00:18:40.350
I wanna live freely!

291
00:18:44.480 --> 00:18:46.270
That's the spirit, Yamato!

292
00:19:00.040 --> 00:19:02.160
It's good to want those things!

293
00:19:03.120 --> 00:19:04.830
Now you know what to do.

294
00:19:13.260 --> 00:19:14.340
Yeah!

295
00:19:19.680 --> 00:19:22.600
And he came home in tatters!

296
00:19:22.600 --> 00:19:27.400
When we were kids, he got us
into all kinds of trouble!

297
00:19:27.400 --> 00:19:29.690
Your little brother sure is something!

298
00:19:29.690 --> 00:19:30.270
Right?!

299
00:19:31.230 --> 00:19:33.610
So tell me, what's it like out there?!

300
00:19:33.610 --> 00:19:36.280
Are there a lot of young up-and-comers?!

301
00:19:36.280 --> 00:19:38.820
Young...? Let me think...

302
00:19:39.240 --> 00:19:41.870
Everyone's talking about Caven-something.

303
00:19:41.870 --> 00:19:43.330
Yeah?!

304
00:19:43.330 --> 00:19:45.910
Well, I'm in a class of my own,

305
00:19:45.910 --> 00:19:49.920
but I heard some dangerous guys
are running wild in every sea.

306
00:19:49.920 --> 00:19:51.250
Mm-hm! Mm-hm!

307
00:19:51.250 --> 00:19:53.380
There's Kid in the south...

308
00:19:53.380 --> 00:19:56.090
Law in the north and Bege in the west.

309
00:19:57.380 --> 00:20:01.010
But the toughest one of all
will set sail in a few years...

310
00:20:01.010 --> 00:20:02.850
My kid brother!

311
00:20:03.890 --> 00:20:06.480
He'll blow 'em all outta the water!

312
00:20:06.480 --> 00:20:09.730
You sure do like to talk about your brother.

313
00:20:09.730 --> 00:20:11.480
So what?! You should listen!

314
00:20:11.480 --> 00:20:13.070
Ow, ow, ow!

315
00:20:13.070 --> 00:20:15.740
You... That hurts!

316
00:20:13.780 --> 00:20:15.740
H-Hey, stop!

317
00:20:20.910 --> 00:20:25.370
The truth is I'm the one
who broke this dragon statue first.

318
00:20:26.540 --> 00:20:28.290
But he said...

319
00:20:28.790 --> 00:20:34.380
"Let this be a warning
to Kaido that I'll be back!"

320
00:20:34.380 --> 00:20:35.920
I see...

321
00:20:35.920 --> 00:20:40.050
I was unaware that a pirate
once tried to save Wano...

322
00:20:40.050 --> 00:20:42.220
It pissed off my father,

323
00:20:42.220 --> 00:20:44.600
but in the end, he never met Ace.

324
00:20:45.430 --> 00:20:46.480
Wait...

325
00:20:46.480 --> 00:20:47.270
Your father?

326
00:20:48.350 --> 00:20:50.810
Didn't I mention Kaido being my father?

327
00:20:54.190 --> 00:20:57.110
Wha– Hey, don't be so scared!

328
00:20:57.110 --> 00:20:59.700
Hey, but I really do hate him!

329
00:20:59.700 --> 00:21:01.740
Like I said, I'm Oden!

330
00:21:01.740 --> 00:21:03.410
That is even more confusing!

331
00:21:03.410 --> 00:21:06.830
I'm not scary! I hate Kaido!

332
00:21:06.830 --> 00:21:11.330
I longed for the sea and adventure,
so I became Oden, who lived freely!

333
00:21:11.330 --> 00:21:13.340
We understand for the most part.

334
00:21:13.340 --> 00:21:15.420
Thank you for tending to us!

335
00:21:15.420 --> 00:21:17.920
Stop being so formal and get over here!

336
00:21:17.920 --> 00:21:19.340
But Yamato,

337
00:21:19.340 --> 00:21:23.010
where is this would-be savior of Wano now?

338
00:21:23.010 --> 00:21:24.300
Ace...

339
00:21:24.300 --> 00:21:26.180
died two years ago.

340
00:21:26.770 --> 00:21:29.390
Otama, you knew Ace?!

341
00:21:29.390 --> 00:21:31.980
Yes, he was like a brother to me!

342
00:21:31.980 --> 00:21:36.570
I decided to believe in Ace
and try to become a kunoichi,

343
00:21:36.570 --> 00:21:39.860
but Big Bro Luffy was mean and said to me...

344
00:21:41.240 --> 00:21:43.950
Ace is dead.

345
00:21:45.030 --> 00:21:46.910
He said it to me out of the blue.

346
00:21:46.910 --> 00:21:49.330
It made me so sad.

347
00:21:49.330 --> 00:21:52.120
Oh, sorry about that.

348
00:21:52.120 --> 00:21:53.710
That's just the way he is.

349
00:21:53.710 --> 00:21:58.000
But y'know, Otama,
it was really hard for Luffy, too.

350
00:21:58.000 --> 00:21:59.590
Back when it happened...

351
00:21:59.010 --> 00:21:59.590
Huh?

352
00:22:01.840 --> 00:22:03.300
He's ruining it!

353
00:22:08.010 --> 00:22:09.680
Listen up, folks!

354
00:22:09.680 --> 00:22:11.690
Put a stop to Marco!

355
00:22:12.640 --> 00:22:15.770
Don't let him run free!

356
00:22:17.190 --> 00:22:20.320
C'mon, he saved us...

357
00:22:20.320 --> 00:22:24.110
But if we don't do what His Awesomeness
wants, he'll kill us anyway...

358
00:22:25.030 --> 00:22:27.280
Don't just stand there!

359
00:22:27.280 --> 00:22:29.410
I gave you an order!

360
00:22:34.420 --> 00:22:38.920
I won't be facing Kaido directly at this point.

361
00:22:39.590 --> 00:22:43.300
Nico Robin! Skeleton Man!
You've got places to be!

362
00:22:43.300 --> 00:22:45.090
Get to the castle!

363
00:22:45.550 --> 00:22:46.800
Now's our chance.

364
00:22:46.800 --> 00:22:48.640
If you insist!

365
00:22:48.640 --> 00:22:51.020
Go to hell, Marco!

366
00:22:58.440 --> 00:23:02.240
You're finished, Marco the Phoenix!

367
00:23:13.080 --> 00:23:14.460
You ready?

368
00:23:14.960 --> 00:23:15.960
Do it!

369
00:23:34.810 --> 00:23:37.190
Damn that Marco!

370
00:23:38.020 --> 00:23:39.310
Nice going!

371
00:23:39.310 --> 00:23:44.280
You're pretty relaxed for someone
about to face down an Emperor!

372
00:23:44.280 --> 00:23:47.160
Why should I be scared of Kaido?

373
00:23:47.160 --> 00:23:50.620
If my captain gives the order, I follow it.

374
00:23:50.620 --> 00:23:54.250
Look at me, rooting for Straw Hat– No...

375
00:23:54.250 --> 00:23:57.290
rooting for all you Worst Generation punks!

376
00:23:58.790 --> 00:24:04.090
I wonder how he would've felt hearing his
brother picked a fight with an Emperor, too...

377
00:24:04.710 --> 00:24:06.300
I'm begging you, Pops!

378
00:24:06.720 --> 00:24:08.800
I said no, you little shit!

379
00:24:11.300 --> 00:24:14.100
Ace, I've told you plenty of times now...

380
00:24:14.890 --> 00:24:20.060
who the 2nd Division
commander was before you...

381
00:24:20.060 --> 00:24:22.690
and why the position was vacant for so long.

382
00:24:22.690 --> 00:24:27.240
Wano practices a policy of isolation,
so information never comes out.

383
00:24:28.030 --> 00:24:33.620
We were unaware that Lord Oden
had died until several years after the fact.

384
00:24:35.290 --> 00:24:40.500
We toyed with the idea of
raiding Wano, but to what end?

385
00:24:40.920 --> 00:24:43.460
Can you imagine the toll it would take?

386
00:24:44.170 --> 00:24:45.670
The toll?

387
00:24:46.050 --> 00:24:48.470
Then, let me go by myself!

388
00:24:51.680 --> 00:24:53.430
I made a promise...

389
00:24:54.640 --> 00:24:58.440
Kozuki Oden couldn't take that guy down...

390
00:25:02.770 --> 00:25:05.650
Meaning you couldn't beat him
on your best day!

391
00:25:05.650 --> 00:25:08.900
Don't overestimate yourself, Ace!

392
00:25:20.670 --> 00:25:23.460
Y'know, Oden's strength was the real deal!

393
00:25:24.130 --> 00:25:28.720
You really wanna take down
the big shots, Commander Ace!

394
00:25:28.720 --> 00:25:31.010
Give it a rest, Teach!

395
00:25:31.010 --> 00:25:34.510
Ace isn't motivated by hunting "big shots."

396
00:25:36.350 --> 00:25:38.220
Dammit...

397
00:25:40.600 --> 00:25:45.020
I need to get stronger
so I can fulfill my promise...

398
00:25:45.020 --> 00:25:49.610
That's what you're shouldering, huh?

399
00:25:49.610 --> 00:25:54.660
Ace, if Pops ever gives the go-ahead,
do not forget to extend an invitation my way.

400
00:25:54.660 --> 00:25:56.700
Count me in, too.

401
00:25:57.370 --> 00:26:00.250
In that case, we can probably
kick his ass now...

402
00:26:02.040 --> 00:26:05.170
How are you still
overestimating the situation...?

403
00:26:18.810 --> 00:26:20.770
Marco!

404
00:26:20.770 --> 00:26:23.770
Don't think we'd just let you through!

405
00:26:23.390 --> 00:26:29.070
<b>Superstar Queen
Ancient Saur-Saur Fruit: Brachiosaurus</b>

406
00:26:23.770 --> 00:26:29.070
Besides, all the samurai up top are dead by now!

407
00:26:29.480 --> 00:26:34.240
And when Kozuki Oden's son
is dead, the battle will be over!

408
00:26:34.280 --> 00:26:39.700
<b>Superstar King
Ancient Saur-Saur Fruit: Pteranodon</b>

409
00:26:34.820 --> 00:26:39.700
Wano shall be reborn as
the pirate empire of New Onigashima!

410
00:26:39.700 --> 00:26:43.580
If that's what you believe,
then you really have a screw loose!

411
00:26:43.580 --> 00:26:45.920
Stop squawking, little bird!

412
00:26:52.590 --> 00:26:54.800
Damn! Is he invincible?!

413
00:26:54.800 --> 00:26:56.720
What kind of power is that?

414
00:26:58.560 --> 00:27:02.600
You're up against the force of a new era now!

415
00:27:02.600 --> 00:27:07.860
The Beast Pirates will crush this "new era,"
along with everything else!

416
00:27:17.200 --> 00:27:18.660
Wha–

417
00:27:21.120 --> 00:27:24.330
Now, now... Just let him pass!

418
00:27:24.330 --> 00:27:25.960
And up you go!

419
00:27:28.290 --> 00:27:30.250
You seriously just threw me?!

420
00:27:42.180 --> 00:27:44.480
What?!

421
00:27:44.480 --> 00:27:45.640
B...

422
00:27:45.640 --> 00:27:50.060
Big Bro Luffy is Ace's little bro?!

423
00:27:50.060 --> 00:27:51.360
That's right.

424
00:27:51.360 --> 00:27:52.860
You didn't know?

425
00:27:52.860 --> 00:27:57.320
Because when I mentioned Ace,
he said so casually...

426
00:27:58.240 --> 00:28:00.070
Ace is dead.

427
00:28:00.950 --> 00:28:04.450
I said some mean things to Big Bro...

428
00:28:04.450 --> 00:28:08.120
He would've been mean right back
if it had bothered him.

429
00:28:08.120 --> 00:28:09.630
Don't worry!

430
00:28:09.630 --> 00:28:10.500
But...

431
00:28:10.920 --> 00:28:15.010
Big Bro... I'm sorry!

432
00:28:15.010 --> 00:28:17.550
Like I said, don't worry.

433
00:28:17.550 --> 00:28:23.350
Anyway, let's give this
"Otama Strategy" of yours a shot!

434
00:28:25.810 --> 00:28:27.810
<b>Forbidden

Storehouse



Inside

the Dome</b>

435
00:28:27.810 --> 00:28:29.400
What?!

436
00:28:29.940 --> 00:28:32.570
This person you speak of was Roger's son,

437
00:28:32.570 --> 00:28:34.570
and Luffy's older brother?!

438
00:28:34.980 --> 00:28:36.820
Is that true?!

439
00:28:36.820 --> 00:28:37.610
Mm-hm.

440
00:28:38.240 --> 00:28:42.740
You all brought Luffy to Wano, right?

441
00:28:42.740 --> 00:28:43.910
That is correct...

442
00:28:44.450 --> 00:28:48.960
There are as many pirates as there are stars
in the sky, but they're the ones you met...

443
00:28:48.960 --> 00:28:51.670
and you brought them to this country...

444
00:28:51.670 --> 00:28:54.250
I can't imagine this as anything but fate!

445
00:28:56.170 --> 00:28:57.470
Because...

446
00:28:58.050 --> 00:29:02.300
Luffy's name bears the initial D!

447
00:29:17.820 --> 00:29:19.570
Yummy!

448
00:29:23.660 --> 00:29:25.620
Fire really hits the spot!

449
00:29:32.250 --> 00:29:34.420
Delicious!

450
00:29:37.090 --> 00:29:42.140
I'm so stuffed now!

451
00:29:42.140 --> 00:29:45.010
I'm fully recharged!

452
00:29:45.010 --> 00:29:47.060
Did you finish your meals?

453
00:29:47.060 --> 00:29:48.560
Yes, Mama!

454
00:29:48.560 --> 00:29:50.180
I'm good to go!

455
00:29:52.190 --> 00:29:54.480
Okay then, let's go!

456
00:30:05.950 --> 00:30:09.160
Straw Hat isn't here yet?

457
00:30:09.160 --> 00:30:11.080
Hey, Kaido!

458
00:30:11.080 --> 00:30:15.920
You can kill as many as you want
as long as you leave Nico Robin alive.

459
00:30:16.790 --> 00:30:21.260
Don't you have a member of the three-eye
people who can read the ancient script?

460
00:30:21.260 --> 00:30:22.800
Oh, Pudding?

461
00:30:22.800 --> 00:30:24.260
I'm not sure she can.

462
00:30:24.260 --> 00:30:27.260
I can't wait for her true awakening anymore.

463
00:30:27.260 --> 00:30:30.980
Yeah, that make sense...

464
00:30:31.020 --> 00:30:34.190
<b>5th Floor

Inside the Castle</b>

465
00:30:34.190 --> 00:30:39.230
This is about all we can do to assist,
so please, go on ahead!

466
00:30:39.230 --> 00:30:41.740
These are the stairs to the rooftop!

467
00:30:42.150 --> 00:30:44.200
Thanks, Shishimamushi!

468
00:30:44.200 --> 00:30:45.870
It's Shishilian.

469
00:30:45.870 --> 00:30:47.990
Yeah, I'll never forget it...

470
00:30:47.990 --> 00:30:52.000
The way you guys defended
Raizo with your lives!

471
00:30:52.410 --> 00:30:53.540
Thank you!

472
00:30:54.290 --> 00:30:55.290
Later!

473
00:31:00.880 --> 00:31:04.010
So where are you planning on
dropping this island?

474
00:31:04.010 --> 00:31:08.140
There is a castle in the Flower Capital
that symbolizes the Kozuki.

475
00:31:11.020 --> 00:31:13.520
I heard they're having a festival.

476
00:31:13.520 --> 00:31:15.480
Quite a lot of people will die.

477
00:31:15.480 --> 00:31:16.850
Who cares?

478
00:31:16.850 --> 00:31:19.400
It's easy to get more slaves...

479
00:31:23.240 --> 00:31:26.240
It'll be a glorious capital.

480
00:31:29.120 --> 00:31:31.410
And the lode poneglyph?

481
00:31:31.410 --> 00:31:32.660
Is it there?

482
00:31:33.790 --> 00:31:36.710
Your true colors are already showing!

483
00:31:36.710 --> 00:31:38.630
Don't give me that!

484
00:31:38.630 --> 00:31:42.960
You're like a little brother to me!

485
00:31:44.380 --> 00:31:47.890
On that day when Rocks
was defeated at God Valley,

486
00:31:47.890 --> 00:31:53.810
I gave you the Mythical Fish-Fish Fruit.

487
00:31:53.810 --> 00:31:57.270
You're indebted to me for life, Kaido!

488
00:31:57.770 --> 00:31:59.650
Whatever!

489
00:32:05.150 --> 00:32:08.240
Let's go get it, then we'll talk!

490
00:32:08.240 --> 00:32:10.910
Let's get the One Piece!
